<section id="lightgbm-model" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="lightgbm-model">LightGBM Model</h2>
<p>In this section, we reproduce the results from the referenced article using the LightGBM model. LightGBM, or Light Gradient Boosting Machine, is a fast and efficient machine learning algorithm that excels at handling large datasets. It is used for both classification and regression tasks. LightGBM works by building an ensemble of decision trees in a sequential manner, where each tree is trained to correct the errors of the previous ones. Unlike other algorithms that grow trees level by level, LightGBM grows trees leaf by leaf, which often results in more accurate models. This approach is guided by gradient descent, which helps minimize errors. LightGBM is designed for speed and scalability, making it suitable for large-scale data. It includes various hyperparameters for fine-tuning, which can significantly improve its performance. This makes LightGBM a popular choice for many machine learning tasks due to its high efficiency and accuracy.</p>
<p>The parameters used in the model are consistent with those specified in the article, ensuring comparability of results. Specifically, we optimized tree-specific parameters: <code>min_child_weight = 2</code>, <code>num_leaves = 36</code>, <code>colsample_bytree = 0.8</code>, <code>learning_rate = 0.15</code>. Additionally, we set the regularization parameter <code>reg_lambda = 0.40</code>.</p>
<section id="data-preparation-for-modeling" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="data-preparation-for-modeling">Data Preparation for Modeling</h3>
<p>We begin with data preparation for modeling such as defining the features and target variable for the model and splitting the dataset into training and testing sets.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb16"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb16-1"><a href="#cb16-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```{r}</span></span>
<span id="cb16-2"><a href="#cb16-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Defining features and target </span></span>
<span id="cb16-3"><a href="#cb16-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>features <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">setdiff</span>(<span class="fu">names</span>(housing_prices_data_clean), <span class="st">&quot;totalPrice&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb16-4"><a href="#cb16-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>target <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="st">&quot;totalPrice&quot;</span></span>
<span id="cb16-5"><a href="#cb16-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb16-6"><a href="#cb16-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Splitting the data into training and testing sets </span></span>
<span id="cb16-7"><a href="#cb16-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">set.seed</span>(<span class="dv">123456789</span>)</span>
<span id="cb16-8"><a href="#cb16-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb16-9"><a href="#cb16-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>data_which_train <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">createDataPartition</span>(housing_prices_data_clean<span class="sc">$</span>totalPrice ,</span>
<span id="cb16-10"><a href="#cb16-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                                        <span class="at">p =</span> <span class="fl">0.8</span>, </span>
<span id="cb16-11"><a href="#cb16-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                                        <span class="at">list =</span> <span class="cn">FALSE</span>) </span>
<span id="cb16-12"><a href="#cb16-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb16-13"><a href="#cb16-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>train_data <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> housing_prices_data_clean[data_which_train,]</span>
<span id="cb16-14"><a href="#cb16-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>test_data <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> housing_prices_data_clean[<span class="sc">-</span>data_which_train,]</span>
<span id="cb16-15"><a href="#cb16-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb16-16"><a href="#cb16-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Preparing data for LightGBM </span></span>
<span id="cb16-17"><a href="#cb16-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>trainMatrix <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">lgb.Dataset</span>(</span>
<span id="cb16-18"><a href="#cb16-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">data =</span> <span class="fu">as.matrix</span>(train_data[, <span class="sc">-</span><span class="fu">which</span>(<span class="fu">names</span>(train_data) <span class="sc">==</span> <span class="st">&quot;totalPrice&quot;</span>)]),</span>
<span id="cb16-19"><a href="#cb16-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">label =</span> train_data<span class="sc">$</span>totalPrice)</span>
<span id="cb16-20"><a href="#cb16-20" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb16-21"><a href="#cb16-21" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>testMatrix <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">lgb.Dataset</span>(</span>
<span id="cb16-22"><a href="#cb16-22" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">data =</span> <span class="fu">as.matrix</span>(test_data[, <span class="sc">-</span><span class="fu">which</span>(<span class="fu">names</span>(test_data) <span class="sc">==</span> <span class="st">&quot;totalPrice&quot;</span>)]),</span>
<span id="cb16-23"><a href="#cb16-23" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">label =</span> test_data<span class="sc">$</span>totalPrice)</span>
<span id="cb16-24"><a href="#cb16-24" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```</span></span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
</div>
</section>
<section id="model-parameters" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="model-parameters">Model Parameters</h3>
<p>The parameters for the LightGBM model are defined based on the article.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb17"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb17-1"><a href="#cb17-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```{r}</span></span>
<span id="cb17-2"><a href="#cb17-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Defining LightGBM parameters based on the article </span></span>
<span id="cb17-3"><a href="#cb17-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>params <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">list</span>(<span class="at">objective =</span> <span class="st">&quot;regression&quot;</span>,</span>
<span id="cb17-4"><a href="#cb17-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>               <span class="at">metric =</span> <span class="st">&quot;rmse&quot;</span>,</span>
<span id="cb17-5"><a href="#cb17-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>               <span class="at">min_child_weight =</span> <span class="dv">2</span>,</span>
<span id="cb17-6"><a href="#cb17-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>               <span class="at">num_leaves =</span> <span class="dv">36</span>,</span>
<span id="cb17-7"><a href="#cb17-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>               <span class="at">colsample_bytree =</span> <span class="fl">0.8</span>,</span>
<span id="cb17-8"><a href="#cb17-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>               <span class="at">reg_lambda =</span> <span class="fl">0.40</span>,</span>
<span id="cb17-9"><a href="#cb17-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>               <span class="at">learning_rate =</span> <span class="fl">0.15</span>,</span>
<span id="cb17-10"><a href="#cb17-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>               <span class="at">feature_fraction =</span> <span class="fl">0.9</span> ) </span>
<span id="cb17-11"><a href="#cb17-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```</span></span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
</div>
</section>
<section id="training-the-model" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="training-the-model">Training the Model</h3>
<p>We train the LightGBM model with the specified parameters.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb18"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb18-1"><a href="#cb18-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```{r message=FALSE, warning=FALSE, results = &quot;hide&quot;}</span></span>
<span id="cb18-2"><a href="#cb18-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Training the LightGBM model  </span></span>
<span id="cb18-3"><a href="#cb18-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>model_lgbm <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">lgb.train</span>(params,</span>
<span id="cb18-4"><a href="#cb18-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                   trainMatrix,</span>
<span id="cb18-5"><a href="#cb18-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                   <span class="at">nrounds =</span> <span class="dv">1000</span>,</span>
<span id="cb18-6"><a href="#cb18-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                   <span class="at">valids =</span> <span class="fu">list</span>(<span class="at">test =</span> testMatrix),</span>
<span id="cb18-7"><a href="#cb18-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                   <span class="at">early_stopping_rounds =</span> <span class="dv">10</span>) </span>
<span id="cb18-8"><a href="#cb18-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```</span></span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
</div>
</section>
<section id="making-predictions" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="making-predictions">Making Predictions</h3>
<p>The model’s predictions are made and adjusted to handle negative values.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb19"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb19-1"><a href="#cb19-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```{r}</span></span>
<span id="cb19-2"><a href="#cb19-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Prediction </span></span>
<span id="cb19-3"><a href="#cb19-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>test_predictions <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">predict</span>(model_lgbm, <span class="fu">as.matrix</span>(test_data[, <span class="sc">-</span><span class="fu">which</span>(<span class="fu">names</span>(test_data) <span class="sc">==</span> <span class="st">&quot;totalPrice&quot;</span>)])) </span>
<span id="cb19-4"><a href="#cb19-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb19-5"><a href="#cb19-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>train_predictions <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">predict</span>(model_lgbm, <span class="fu">as.matrix</span>(train_data[, <span class="sc">-</span><span class="fu">which</span>(<span class="fu">names</span>(train_data) <span class="sc">==</span> <span class="st">&quot;totalPrice&quot;</span>)]))  </span>
<span id="cb19-6"><a href="#cb19-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb19-7"><a href="#cb19-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Excluding negative predicted values </span></span>
<span id="cb19-8"><a href="#cb19-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>test_predictions <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">ifelse</span>(test_predictions <span class="sc">&lt;</span> <span class="dv">0</span>, <span class="fl">0.01</span>, test_predictions)</span>
<span id="cb19-9"><a href="#cb19-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>train_predictions <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">ifelse</span>(train_predictions <span class="sc">&lt;</span> <span class="dv">0</span>, <span class="fl">0.01</span>, train_predictions) </span>
<span id="cb19-10"><a href="#cb19-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```</span></span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
</div>
</section>
<section id="evaluation-metrics" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="evaluation-metrics">Evaluation Metrics</h3>
<p>We evaluate the model using RMSLE and MAPE metrics.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb20"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb20-1"><a href="#cb20-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```{r}</span></span>
<span id="cb20-2"><a href="#cb20-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Evaluation metrics </span></span>
<span id="cb20-3"><a href="#cb20-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb20-4"><a href="#cb20-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># RMSLE and MAPE for test data </span></span>
<span id="cb20-5"><a href="#cb20-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>test_rmsle_score <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">rmsle</span>(test_data[[target]], test_predictions)</span>
<span id="cb20-6"><a href="#cb20-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>test_mape_score <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">mape</span>(test_data[[target]], test_predictions)  </span>
<span id="cb20-7"><a href="#cb20-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb20-8"><a href="#cb20-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># RMSLE and MAPE for train data </span></span>
<span id="cb20-9"><a href="#cb20-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>train_rmsle_score <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">rmsle</span>(train_data[[target]], train_predictions)</span>
<span id="cb20-10"><a href="#cb20-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>train_mape_score <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">mape</span>(train_data[[target]], train_predictions)  </span>
<span id="cb20-11"><a href="#cb20-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb20-12"><a href="#cb20-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">cat</span>(<span class="st">&quot;Test RMSLE: &quot;</span>, test_rmsle_score, <span class="st">&quot;</span><span class="sc">\n</span><span class="st">&quot;</span>) </span>
<span id="cb20-13"><a href="#cb20-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">cat</span>(<span class="st">&quot;Test MAPE: &quot;</span>, test_mape_score, <span class="st">&quot;</span><span class="sc">\n</span><span class="st">&quot;</span>) </span>
<span id="cb20-14"><a href="#cb20-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">cat</span>(<span class="st">&quot;Train RMSLE: &quot;</span>, train_rmsle_score, <span class="st">&quot;</span><span class="sc">\n</span><span class="st">&quot;</span>) </span>
<span id="cb20-15"><a href="#cb20-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">cat</span>(<span class="st">&quot;Train MAPE: &quot;</span>, train_mape_score, <span class="st">&quot;</span><span class="sc">\n</span><span class="st">&quot;</span>) </span>
<span id="cb20-16"><a href="#cb20-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```</span></span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
<div class="cell-output cell-output-stdout">
<pre><code>Test RMSLE:  0.1501456 
Test MAPE:  0.17798 
Train RMSLE:  0.1391439 
Train MAPE:  0.1163801 </code></pre>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<span id="cb22-33"><a href="#cb22-33" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="at">subtitle =</span> <span class="st">&quot;Train Data&quot;</span></span>

<span id="cb22-35"><a href="#cb22-35" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">scale_x_continuous</span>(<span class="at">labels =</span> scales<span class="sc">::</span><span class="fu">label_number</span>(<span class="at">scale =</span> <span class="fl">1e-6</span>, <span class="at">suffix =</span> <span class="st">&quot;M&quot;</span>)) <span class="sc">+</span></span>
<span id="cb22-36"><a href="#cb22-36" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">scale_y_continuous</span>(<span class="at">labels =</span> scales<span class="sc">::</span><span class="fu">label_number</span>(<span class="at">scale =</span> <span class="fl">1e-6</span>, <span class="at">suffix =</span> <span class="st">&quot;M&quot;</span>)) <span class="sc">+</span>  </span>
<span id="cb22-37"><a href="#cb22-37" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">theme_minimal</span>() <span class="sc">+</span></span>
<span id="cb22-38"><a href="#cb22-38" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">theme</span>(<span class="at">plot.title =</span> <span class="fu">element_blank</span>()) </span>
<span id="cb22-39"><a href="#cb22-39" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb22-40"><a href="#cb22-40" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">grid.arrange</span>(train_p, test_p, <span class="at">ncol =</span> <span class="dv">2</span>)</span>
<span id="cb22-41"><a href="#cb22-41" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```</span></span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
<div class="cell-output-display">
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," class="img-fluid" width="672"></p>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li><p>Our <strong>test RMSLE</strong> of 0.1501 is slightly better than the article’s test RMSLE of 0.1694.</p></li>
<li><p>Our <strong>train RMSLE</strong> of 0.1391 is also better than the article’s train RMSLE of 0.1669.</p></li>
<li><p>We also included MAPE as an additional metric, providing further insight into the model’s accuracy. Our <strong>test MAPE</strong> is 0.178, and <strong>train MAPE</strong> is 0.1164.</p></li>
<li><p>The number of estimators in our model was 387, significantly higher than the 64 estimators used in the article. This difference indicates that our model required more trees to achieve optimal performance, which might be due to differences in data preprocessing or parameter tuning.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>In conclusion, our LightGBM model performs comparably to the one in the referenced article, with a slightly better fit on the training data. The inclusion of MAPE gives us a clearer picture of prediction errors, emphasizing the model’s practical accuracy in terms of percentage error.</p>
</section>
</section>
<section id="hybrid-regression" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="hybrid-regression">Hybrid Regression</h2>
<p>In this section, we describe the creation and evaluation of a hybrid regression model that combines the predictions from three different machine learning models: RandomForest, XGBoost, and LightGBM. Each model contributes equally to the final prediction, enhancing the robustness and accuracy of the prediction by leveraging the strengths of each individual model.</p>
<section id="loading-models-and-generating-predictions" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="loading-models-and-generating-predictions">Loading Models and Generating Predictions</h3>
<p>We begin by loading the pre-trained models for RandomForest and XGBoost and LightGBM. After loading these models, we generate predictions for the test dataset.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb23"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb23-1"><a href="#cb23-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```{r message=FALSE, warning=FALSE, results = &quot;hide&quot;}</span></span>
<span id="cb23-2"><a href="#cb23-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>data_rf <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">readRDS</span>(<span class="st">&quot;data_rf_model.rds&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb23-3"><a href="#cb23-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>data_xgboost <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">readRDS</span>(<span class="st">&quot;data_xgboost_model.rds&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb23-4"><a href="#cb23-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb23-5"><a href="#cb23-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">source</span>(<span class="st">&quot;RR_HousingPricePred_LightGBM.R&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb23-6"><a href="#cb23-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb23-7"><a href="#cb23-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">load</span>(<span class="st">&quot;housing_prices_data_clean.Rdata&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb23-8"><a href="#cb23-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">set.seed</span>(<span class="dv">123456789</span>)</span>
<span id="cb23-9"><a href="#cb23-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>data_which_train <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">createDataPartition</span>(housing_prices_data_clean<span class="sc">$</span>totalPrice ,</span>
<span id="cb23-10"><a href="#cb23-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                                        <span class="at">p =</span> <span class="fl">0.8</span>,</span>
<span id="cb23-11"><a href="#cb23-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                                        <span class="at">list =</span> <span class="cn">FALSE</span>) </span>
<span id="cb23-12"><a href="#cb23-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb23-13"><a href="#cb23-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>data_train <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> housing_prices_data_clean[data_which_train,]</span>
<span id="cb23-14"><a href="#cb23-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>data_test <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> housing_prices_data_clean[<span class="sc">-</span>data_which_train,]</span>
<span id="cb23-15"><a href="#cb23-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb23-16"><a href="#cb23-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>pred_rf_test <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">predict</span>(data_rf, data_test)</span>
<span id="cb23-17"><a href="#cb23-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>pred_xgb_test <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">predict</span>(data_xgboost, data_test)</span>
<span id="cb23-18"><a href="#cb23-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>pred_lgb_test <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">predict</span>(model_lgbm, <span class="fu">as.matrix</span>(data_test[, <span class="sc">-</span><span class="fu">which</span>(<span class="fu">names</span>(data_test) <span class="sc">==</span> <span class="st">&quot;totalPrice&quot;</span>)]))</span>
<span id="cb23-19"><a href="#cb23-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb23-20"><a href="#cb23-20" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>pred_rf_train <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">predict</span>(data_rf, data_train)</span>
<span id="cb23-21"><a href="#cb23-21" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>pred_xgb_train <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">predict</span>(data_xgboost, data_train)</span>
<span id="cb23-22"><a href="#cb23-22" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>pred_lgb_train <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">predict</span>(model_lgbm, </span>
<span id="cb23-23"><a href="#cb23-23" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                          <span class="fu">as.matrix</span>(data_train[, <span class="sc">-</span><span class="fu">which</span>(<span class="fu">names</span>(data_train) <span class="sc">==</span> <span class="st">&quot;totalPrice&quot;</span>)]))</span>
<span id="cb23-24"><a href="#cb23-24" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```</span></span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
</div>
</section>
<section id="combining-predictions" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="combining-predictions">Combining Predictions</h3>
<p>The predictions from the three models are combined using a simple average. This approach ensures that each model’s prediction contributes equally to the final prediction.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb24"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb24-1"><a href="#cb24-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```{r}</span></span>
<span id="cb24-2"><a href="#cb24-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>combined_predictions_test <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> (pred_rf_test <span class="sc">+</span> pred_xgb_test <span class="sc">+</span> pred_lgb_test) <span class="sc">/</span> <span class="dv">3</span></span>
<span id="cb24-3"><a href="#cb24-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>combined_predictions_train <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> (pred_rf_train <span class="sc">+</span> pred_xgb_train <span class="sc">+</span> pred_lgb_train) <span class="sc">/</span> <span class="dv">3</span></span>
<span id="cb24-4"><a href="#cb24-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb24-5"><a href="#cb24-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>combined_predictions_test <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">ifelse</span>(combined_predictions_test <span class="sc">&lt;</span> <span class="dv">0</span>,</span>
<span id="cb24-6"><a href="#cb24-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                                    <span class="fl">0.01</span>, combined_predictions_test)</span>
<span id="cb24-7"><a href="#cb24-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>combined_predictions_train <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">ifelse</span>(combined_predictions_train <span class="sc">&lt;</span> <span class="dv">0</span>, </span>
<span id="cb24-8"><a href="#cb24-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                                     <span class="fl">0.01</span>, combined_predictions_train)</span>
<span id="cb24-9"><a href="#cb24-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```</span></span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
</div>
</section>
<section id="evaluating-the-hybrid-model" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="evaluating-the-hybrid-model">Evaluating the Hybrid Model</h3>
<p>We evaluate the performance of the hybrid model using two key metrics: Root Mean Squared Logarithmic Error (RMSLE) and Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE). These metrics provide a clear picture of the model’s accuracy in predicting housing prices.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb25"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb25-1"><a href="#cb25-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```{r}</span></span>
<span id="cb25-2"><a href="#cb25-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>combined_rmsle_test <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> Metrics<span class="sc">::</span><span class="fu">rmsle</span>(data_test<span class="sc">$</span>totalPrice,</span>
<span id="cb25-3"><a href="#cb25-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                                      combined_predictions_test)</span>
<span id="cb25-4"><a href="#cb25-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>combined_mape_test <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> Metrics<span class="sc">::</span><span class="fu">mape</span>(data_test<span class="sc">$</span>totalPrice, </span>
<span id="cb25-5"><a href="#cb25-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                                    combined_predictions_test)</span>
<span id="cb25-6"><a href="#cb25-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb25-7"><a href="#cb25-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">cat</span>(<span class="st">&quot;Combined Test RMSLE: &quot;</span>, combined_rmsle_test, <span class="st">&quot;</span><span class="sc">\n</span><span class="st">&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb25-8"><a href="#cb25-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">cat</span>(<span class="st">&quot;Combined Test MAPE: &quot;</span>, combined_mape_test, <span class="st">&quot;</span><span class="sc">\n</span><span class="st">&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb25-9"><a href="#cb25-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb25-10"><a href="#cb25-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>combined_rmsle_train <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> Metrics<span class="sc">::</span><span class="fu">rmsle</span>(train_data<span class="sc">$</span>totalPrice,</span>
<span id="cb25-11"><a href="#cb25-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                                      combined_predictions_train)</span>
<span id="cb25-12"><a href="#cb25-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>combined_mape_train <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> Metrics<span class="sc">::</span><span class="fu">mape</span>(train_data<span class="sc">$</span>totalPrice, </span>
<span id="cb25-13"><a href="#cb25-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                                    combined_predictions_train)</span>
<span id="cb25-14"><a href="#cb25-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb25-15"><a href="#cb25-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">cat</span>(<span class="st">&quot;Combined Train RMSLE: &quot;</span>, combined_rmsle_train, <span class="st">&quot;</span><span class="sc">\n</span><span class="st">&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb25-16"><a href="#cb25-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">cat</span>(<span class="st">&quot;Combined Train MAPE: &quot;</span>, combined_mape_train, <span class="st">&quot;</span><span class="sc">\n</span><span class="st">&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb25-17"><a href="#cb25-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```</span></span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
<div class="cell-output cell-output-stdout">
<pre><code>Combined Test RMSLE:  0.1434729 
Combined Test MAPE:  0.1566243 
Combined Train RMSLE:  0.1370518 
Combined Train MAPE:  0.1172748 </code></pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>We compare the results of our hybrid model with those reported in the referenced article. The article reported a Train RMSLE of 0.14969 and a Test RMSLE of 0.16372.</p>
<p>Our hybrid model achieved:</p>
<ul>
<li><p><strong>Train RMSLE</strong>: 0.1371</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Test RMSLE</strong>: 0.1435</p></li>
</ul>
<p>These results indicate that our model performs better than the article’s model, both on the training and test data.</p>
</section>
<section id="plotting-the-results" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="plotting-the-results">Plotting the Results</h3>
<p>Finally, we visualize the performance of the hybrid model by plotting the actual vs. predicted prices. The plot includes a regression line to illustrate the relationship between predicted and actual prices.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb27"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb27-1"><a href="#cb27-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```{r}</span></span>

<span id="cb27-12"><a href="#cb27-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">scale_y_continuous</span>(<span class="at">labels =</span> scales<span class="sc">::</span><span class="fu">label_number</span>(<span class="at">scale =</span> <span class="fl">1e-6</span>, <span class="at">suffix =</span> <span class="st">&quot;M&quot;</span>)) <span class="sc">+</span>  </span>
<span id="cb27-13"><a href="#cb27-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">theme_minimal</span>() <span class="sc">+</span></span>

<span id="cb27-15"><a href="#cb27-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```</span></span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
<div class="cell-output-display">
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," class="img-fluid" width="672"></p>
</div>
</div>
<p>In summary, the hybrid regression model combines predictions from RandomForest, XGBoost, and LightGBM to improve the overall prediction accuracy. By averaging the predictions, we leverage the strengths of each model, resulting in a robust and reliable prediction system. Our hybrid model outperforms the referenced model, achieving lower RMSLE on both training and test datasets.</p>
</section>
</section>
<section id="stacked-generalization" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="stacked-generalization">Stacked Generalization</h2>
<p>Stacked generalization involves amalgamating the outcomes of individual estimators and employing a regressor to generate the ultimate prediction. This technique leverages the capabilities of each individual estimator by employing their outputs as inputs for a final estimator.</p>
<p>The fundamental concept of this method revolves around utilizing the forecasts generated by preceding models as attributes for another model. Additionally, this strategy incorporates the k-fold cross-validation technique to mitigate the risk of overfitting.</p>
<p>This study employed a prevalent 2-level stacking architecture to predict housing prices. In the initial stacking level, Random Forest and LightGBM were utilized, while XGBoost constituted the second stacking level. Additionally, to accommodate the relatively large dataset, the stacking model was subjected to 5-fold cross-validation.</p>
<p>Our Stacked Generalization model achieved:</p>

    <p>Train RMSLE: 0.294</p>

    <p>Test RMSLE: 0.304</p>

<p>These results indicate that our model performs worse than the article’s model, both on the training and test data.</p>


</section>
<section id="conclusions" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="conclusions">Conclusions</h2>
<p>* We got the expected results, and in the case of Hybrid Regression and LightGBM even better than the authors of the article
</p>
<p>* LightGBM and Hybrid Regression gave us better results than researchers'
</p>
<p>* For RF, XGBoost and Stacked Generalization we obtained worse results.
</p>
<p>* The training set exhibits lower error rates compared to the test set, suggesting a degree of overfitting.

</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb28"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb28-1"><a href="#cb28-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="in">```{r}</span></span>
<span id="cb28-2"><a href="#cb28-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#regressionMetrics</span></span>

<script id="quarto-html-after-body" type="application/javascript">
window.document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function (event) {
  const toggleBodyColorMode = (bsSheetEl) => {
    const mode = bsSheetEl.getAttribute("data-mode");
    const bodyEl = window.document.querySelector("body");
    if (mode === "dark") {
      bodyEl.classList.add("quarto-dark");
      bodyEl.classList.remove("quarto-light");
    } else {
      bodyEl.classList.add("quarto-light");
      bodyEl.classList.remove("quarto-dark");
    }
  }
  const toggleBodyColorPrimary = () => {
    const bsSheetEl = window.document.querySelector("link#quarto-bootstrap");
    if (bsSheetEl) {
      toggleBodyColorMode(bsSheetEl);
    }
  }
  toggleBodyColorPrimary();  
  const icon = "";
  const anchorJS = new window.AnchorJS();
  anchorJS.options = {
    placement: 'right',
    icon: icon
  };
  anchorJS.add('.anchored');
  const isCodeAnnotation = (el) => {
    for (const clz of el.classList) {
      if (clz.startsWith('code-annotation-')) {                     
        return true;
      }
    }
    return false;
  }
  const clipboard = new window.ClipboardJS('.code-copy-button', {
    text: function(trigger) {
      const codeEl = trigger.previousElementSibling.cloneNode(true);
      for (const childEl of codeEl.children) {
        if (isCodeAnnotation(childEl)) {
          childEl.remove();
        }
      }
      return codeEl.innerText;
    }
  });
  clipboard.on('success', function(e) {
    // button target
    const button = e.trigger;
    // don't keep focus
    button.blur();
    // flash "checked"
    button.classList.add('code-copy-button-checked');
    var currentTitle = button.getAttribute("title");
    button.setAttribute("title", "Copied!");
    let tooltip;
    if (window.bootstrap) {
      button.setAttribute("data-bs-toggle", "tooltip");
      button.setAttribute("data-bs-placement", "left");
      button.setAttribute("data-bs-title", "Copied!");
      tooltip = new bootstrap.Tooltip(button, 
        { trigger: "manual", 
          customClass: "code-copy-button-tooltip",
          offset: [0, -8]});
      tooltip.show();    
    }
    setTimeout(function() {
      if (tooltip) {
        tooltip.hide();
        button.removeAttribute("data-bs-title");
        button.removeAttribute("data-bs-toggle");
        button.removeAttribute("data-bs-placement");
      }
      button.setAttribute("title", currentTitle);
      button.classList.remove('code-copy-button-checked');
    }, 1000);
    // clear code selection
    e.clearSelection();
  });
  function tippyHover(el, contentFn) {
    const config = {
      allowHTML: true,
      content: contentFn,
      maxWidth: 500,
      delay: 100,
      arrow: false,
      appendTo: function(el) {
          return el.parentElement;
      },
      interactive: true,
      interactiveBorder: 10,
      theme: 'quarto',
      placement: 'bottom-start'
    };
    window.tippy(el, config); 
  }
  const noterefs = window.document.querySelectorAll('a[role="doc-noteref"]');
  for (var i=0; i<noterefs.length; i++) {
    const ref = noterefs[i];
    tippyHover(ref, function() {
      // use id or data attribute instead here
      let href = ref.getAttribute('data-footnote-href') || ref.getAttribute('href');
      try { href = new URL(href).hash; } catch {}
      const id = href.replace(/^#\/?/, "");
      const note = window.document.getElementById(id);
      return note.innerHTML;
    });
  }
      let selectedAnnoteEl;
      const selectorForAnnotation = ( cell, annotation) => {
        let cellAttr = 'data-code-cell="' + cell + '"';
        let lineAttr = 'data-code-annotation="' +  annotation + '"';
        const selector = 'span[' + cellAttr + '][' + lineAttr + ']';
        return selector;
      }
      const selectCodeLines = (annoteEl) => {
        const doc = window.document;
        const targetCell = annoteEl.getAttribute("data-target-cell");
        const targetAnnotation = annoteEl.getAttribute("data-target-annotation");
        const annoteSpan = window.document.querySelector(selectorForAnnotation(targetCell, targetAnnotation));
        const lines = annoteSpan.getAttribute("data-code-lines").split(",");
        const lineIds = lines.map((line) => {
          return targetCell + "-" + line;
        })
        let top = null;
        let height = null;
        let parent = null;
        if (lineIds.length > 0) {
            //compute the position of the single el (top and bottom and make a div)
            const el = window.document.getElementById(lineIds[0]);
            top = el.offsetTop;
            height = el.offsetHeight;
            parent = el.parentElement.parentElement;
          if (lineIds.length > 1) {
            const lastEl = window.document.getElementById(lineIds[lineIds.length - 1]);
            const bottom = lastEl.offsetTop + lastEl.offsetHeight;
            height = bottom - top;
          }
          if (top !== null && height !== null && parent !== null) {
            // cook up a div (if necessary) and position it 
            let div = window.document.getElementById("code-annotation-line-highlight");
            if (div === null) {
              div = window.document.createElement("div");
              div.setAttribute("id", "code-annotation-line-highlight");
              div.style.position = 'absolute';
              parent.appendChild(div);
            }
            div.style.top = top - 2 + "px";
            div.style.height = height + 4 + "px";
            let gutterDiv = window.document.getElementById("code-annotation-line-highlight-gutter");
            if (gutterDiv === null) {
              gutterDiv = window.document.createElement("div");
              gutterDiv.setAttribute("id", "code-annotation-line-highlight-gutter");
              gutterDiv.style.position = 'absolute';
              const codeCell = window.document.getElementById(targetCell);
              const gutter = codeCell.querySelector('.code-annotation-gutter');
              gutter.appendChild(gutterDiv);
            }
            gutterDiv.style.top = top - 2 + "px";
            gutterDiv.style.height = height + 4 + "px";
          }
          selectedAnnoteEl = annoteEl;
        }
      };
      const unselectCodeLines = () => {
        const elementsIds = ["code-annotation-line-highlight", "code-annotation-line-highlight-gutter"];
        elementsIds.forEach((elId) => {
          const div = window.document.getElementById(elId);
          if (div) {
            div.remove();
          }
        });
        selectedAnnoteEl = undefined;
      };
      // Attach click handler to the DT
      const annoteDls = window.document.querySelectorAll('dt[data-target-cell]');
      for (const annoteDlNode of annoteDls) {
        annoteDlNode.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
          const clickedEl = event.target;
          if (clickedEl !== selectedAnnoteEl) {
            unselectCodeLines();
            const activeEl = window.document.querySelector('dt[data-target-cell].code-annotation-active');
            if (activeEl) {
              activeEl.classList.remove('code-annotation-active');
            }
            selectCodeLines(clickedEl);
            clickedEl.classList.add('code-annotation-active');
          } else {
            // Unselect the line
            unselectCodeLines();
            clickedEl.classList.remove('code-annotation-active');
          }
        });
      }
  const findCites = (el) => {
    const parentEl = el.parentElement;
    if (parentEl) {
      const cites = parentEl.dataset.cites;
      if (cites) {
        return {
          el,
          cites: cites.split(' ')
        };
      } else {
        return findCites(el.parentElement)
      }
    } else {
      return undefined;
    }
  };
  var bibliorefs = window.document.querySelectorAll('a[role="doc-biblioref"]');
  for (var i=0; i<bibliorefs.length; i++) {
    const ref = bibliorefs[i];
    const citeInfo = findCites(ref);
    if (citeInfo) {
      tippyHover(citeInfo.el, function() {
        var popup = window.document.createElement('div');
        citeInfo.cites.forEach(function(cite) {
          var citeDiv = window.document.createElement('div');
          citeDiv.classList.add('hanging-indent');
          citeDiv.classList.add('csl-entry');
          var biblioDiv = window.document.getElementById('ref-' + cite);
          if (biblioDiv) {
            citeDiv.innerHTML = biblioDiv.innerHTML;
          }
          popup.appendChild(citeDiv);
        });
        return popup.innerHTML;
      });
    }
  }
});
</script>
</div> <!-- /content -->



</body></html>
